description: This trap is sent each time an alarm condition is raised and
inserted into to the cmSysAlmTable.
It is also sent each time an
alarm condition is cleared and removed from the
cmSysAlmTable.
objects.test: $SNMPTRAPCMD CM-ALARM-MIB::cmSysAlmTrap CM-ALARM-MIB::cmAlmIndex i 9999 CM-ALARM-MIB::cmSysAlmNotifCode i 2 CM-ALARM-MIB::cmSysAlmType i 0 CM-ALARM-MIB::cmSysAlmSrvEff i 2 CM-ALARM-MIB::cmSysAlmTime s EXAMPLEE CM-ALARM-MIB::cmSysAlmLocation i 0 CM-ALARM-MIB::cmSysAlmDirection i 0 CM-ALARM-MIB::cmSysAlmDescr s EXAMPLE CM-ALARM-MIB::cmSysAlmObject o 1.3.6.1.4.1.8072.2.1.1 CM-ALARM-MIB::cmSysAlmObjectName s EXAMPLE CM-ALARM-MIB::cmSysAlmAdditionalInfoObject o 1.3.6.1.4.1.8072.2.1.1 CM-ALARM-MIB::cmSysAlmAdditionalInfoName s EXAMPLE

description: This value is assigned globally and sequentially to each new
trap that is sent from the device.
When this value reaches a maximum of 65535, it is wrapped to
the value 1.
variables.name: CM-ALARM-MIB::cmAlmIndex

description: This object identifies the severity of the condition.
variables.name: CM-ALARM-MIB::cmSysAlmNotifCode

description: This object identifies the type of the condition.
variables.name: CM-ALARM-MIB::cmSysAlmType

description: This object identifies whether the condition is service affecting
or not.
variables.name: CM-ALARM-MIB::cmSysAlmSrvEff

description: This object contains the system time when the condition occurred.
variables.name: CM-ALARM-MIB::cmSysAlmTime

description: This object identifies the location of the condition. The value
none(0) should be used if location is not applicable.
variables.name: CM-ALARM-MIB::cmSysAlmLocation

description: This object identifies the direction of the condition. The value
none(0) should be used if direction is not applicable.
variables.name: CM-ALARM-MIB::cmSysAlmDirection

description: This object contains a text description of the condition.
variables.name: CM-ALARM-MIB::cmSysAlmDescr

description: OID of the actual object that raised the alarm.
variables.name: CM-ALARM-MIB::cmSysAlmObject

description: Symbolic name of the managed object to which the condition
pertains.
variables.name: CM-ALARM-MIB::cmSysAlmObjectName

description: This object provides OID of associated entity that caused the alarm.
If there is no associated entity, this value is 0.0.
variables.name: CM-ALARM-MIB::cmSysAlmAdditionalInfoObject

description: This object provides name of the associated entity to which the
alarm pertains. If there is no such entity, this value is empty.
variables.name: CM-ALARM-MIB::cmSysAlmAdditionalInfoName

description: This trap is sent each time an alarm condition is raised and
inserted into to the cmNetworkElementAlmTable.

alarm condition is cleared and removed from the
cmNetworkElementAlmTable.

description: This trap is sent each time an event condition is raised and
inserted into to the cmSysCondTable.
It is also sent each time an
event condition is cleared and removed from the
cmSysCondTable. Standing conditions/transient conditions
are reported using this notification.
